 The National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has nominated Governor Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom to head the committee to conduct the party’s governorship primary in Ekiti State. In a statement released on Tuesday by the party’s National Organizing Secretary, Hon. Umar Bature, the party said the five-man committee is mandated to elect the party’s gubernatorial candidate for the upcoming governorship election in the state.
The governorship primary election will hold tomorrow, Wednesday, January 26, in Ado Ekiti, the state capital. Others who are members of the committee include the former deputy governor of Osun State, Erelu Olusola Obada, Hon. Michael Mku, Ibrahim Khalid and Rt. Hon. Toby Okechukwu, who will serve as member/secretary of the committee. The full statement reads: “The National Working Committee of our great party, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has nominated the following party members to serve on the Electoral Committee to conduct Special State Congress in Ekiti State. “The Committee is mandated to elect our party’s gubernatorial candidate for the upcoming Governorship Election in the State.
Composition H.E. Chief Udom Emmanuel (Chairman) H.E. Erelu Olusola Obada (Member) Hon. Michael Mku (Member) Barr. Ibrahim Khalid (Member) Rt. Hon. Toby Okechukwu (Member/Secretary) “The exercise is scheduled for Wednesday, January 26, 2022, at the State Capital, Ado Ekiti, Ekiti State.” 